---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import SignupForm from '@/components/SignupForm.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Membership | YIMBY Adelaide"
  description="Become a YIMBY Adelaide member and help build a stronger pro-housing voice for Adelaide."
>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero page-hero--membership">
      <p class="eyebrow">Membership</p>
      <h1>Become a founding member of YIMBY Adelaide.</h1>
      <p>
        Help build a durable, local, pro-housing organisation that can advocate for more homes,
        better choices, and a fairer Adelaide.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href="#apply">Apply to join</a>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="#principles">How membership works</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Why Join</p>
        <h2>Membership makes the movement harder to ignore.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="copy-stack">
        <p>
          Signing up is the first step. Membership is for people who want to help YIMBY Adelaide
          become a serious civic voice in planning, transport, housing, and local government debates.
        </p>
        <p>
          Members help fund the practical work: research, submissions, community events, campaign
          tools, design, hosting, and the boring-but-important administration that makes advocacy last.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section member-options" aria-label="Membership options">
      <article class="member-card member-card--primary">
        <p class="eyebrow">Recommended</p>
        <h2>Founding Member</h2>
        <p class="member-card__price">$10 per month</p>
        <p>
          A simple recurring contribution to help YIMBY Adelaide launch, organise, and speak up for
          housing abundance.
        </p>
        <a class="button" href="#apply">Start membership</a>
      </article>

      <article class="member-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Accessible</p>
        <h2>Supporter Member</h2>
        <p class="member-card__price">$25 per year</p>
        <p>
          A lower-cost option for students, renters, unwaged supporters, or anyone who wants to be
          involved without a monthly contribution.
        </p>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="#apply">Choose supporter</a>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="section values" id="principles">
      <article>
        <span>01</span>
        <h3>Member Voice</h3>
        <p>Members help shape priorities, campaign focus, and the organisation we are building.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>02</span>
        <h3>Practical Advocacy</h3>
        <p>Membership funds submissions, research, events, campaign materials, and public education.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>03</span>
        <h3>Independence</h3>
        <p>We will be transparent about funding and avoid conflicts that weaken public trust.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>04</span>
        <h3>Local Focus</h3>
        <p>Our work starts with Adelaide: homes near jobs, services, transport, schools, and community.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="section split probity-section">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Probity</p>
        <h2>We need trust as much as money.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="copy-stack">
        <p>
          YIMBY Adelaide should be funded by people who want a fairer housing system, not by interests
          seeking special treatment.
        </p>
        <p>
          Before paid memberships go live, we will publish clear rules about donations, conflicts of
          interest, governance, and what kinds of support we will not accept.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section application-band" id="apply">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Apply</p>
        <h2>Membership payments are coming next.</h2>
        <p>
          For now, join the list and tick membership interest when the Action Network form loads.
          We will connect the payment flow once the membership provider is chosen.
        </p>
      </div>
      <SignupForm compact />
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
